14/09/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn again called for the acceleration of reforms in Albania, during a phone conversation Tuesday (13 September) with the country's new Prime Minister Sali Berisha. Rehn pledged continued support for Albania's EU aspirations but stressed that Tirana is expected to step up integration-related reforms as well as the fight against crime and corruption. (Albanian Government Web site - 13/09/05)
